Automatic sanity-testing: FAILED BUILD/TEST, see http://jenkins.bluematt.me/pull-tester/p4940_62e5f8f96114a872354103ef566b5c74a16154d4/ for binaries and test log.

This could happen for one of several reasons:
1. It chanages paths in makefile.linux-mingw or otherwise changes build scripts in a way that made them incompatible with the automated testing scripts (please tweak those patches in qa/p
You can simulate strnlen(s, n) with memchr(s, 0, n) in this case.\n

Yeah - I'm just a bit reluctant to change the code from the current obvious state just to make a compiler happy that no one is using anymore. As it's working fine in travis and the compiler that is used to build releases. I'd rather just wait for pulltester to die (#4907).\n
